Course consists the lectures of stage production and organising regulations of performing arts´ working environment. Students write and defend their own performing arts´ projects.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide the basic knowledges and skills for independant performing arts´ production and to give the overview of organising regulations of performing arts´ working environment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course student:  -is able to understand and use the basic concepts and themes of stage production; -is able to understand the main traits of culture politics (esp. theatre politics) in Estonia; -knows the different types of contracts and basics of copyrights; -knows and is able to use the safety instructions in performing arts´s institutions (esp. theatres); -is able to write the production project of the independant performance.
